| **House 16** | Changes that happen slowly and with difficulty. | A journey that will be difficult but ultimately successful. | A clear path forward, indicating success and enlightenment. | A union of people or ideas that leads to success. | A gentle, nurturing home and family life. | A loss that ultimately leads to new opportunities. | Great luck and prosperity. | Small luck or a minor victory. | A difficult choice that must be made in order to move forward. | Letting go of the past in order to move forward. | Joy, happiness, and celebration. | Grief and mourning, sadness. | Imprisonment, feeling trapped or stuck. | Acquisition of wealth or material possessions. | Energy, impulsiveness, and enthusiasm. |
| **House 15** | Uncertainty and confusion in matters of health or illness. | A difficult or delayed journey. | Success in business or intellectual pursuits. | A connection or bond that is strong but not necessarily romantic. | A nurturing and compassionate caretaker. | A major loss, often related to money or a relationship. | Great success and good fortune in matters of wealth or career. | Small successes or minor gains. | An event or situation that will ultimately lead to personal growth. | A difficult or traumatic event from the past that is still affecting the present. | Happiness and contentment in all areas of life. | Feeling of isolation or loneliness. | Feeling trapped or stuck in a relationship or situation. | Gaining wealth or material possessions through hard work or effort. | Youth, impulsiveness, and reckless behavior. |
| **House 14** | Hidden health problems or illness that has not yet been diagnosed. | A journey with many twists and turns, possibly ending in disappointment. | A clear and successful path forward, often related to intellectual or spiritual pursuits. | A deep and meaningful connection between people, often romantic in nature. | A caring and nurturing family life. | A significant financial loss, often related to investments or gambling. | Great success and good fortune in matters of spiritual or intellectual growth. | Small victories or gains in personal growth or spiritual pursuits. | Personal growth through sacrifice or loss. | Releasing old patterns or beliefs that are holding you back. | Happiness and joy related to personal growth and spiritual development. | Feelings of sadness or grief related to personal growth or spiritual development. | Feeling trapped or stuck in a mental or emotional pattern. | Gaining wealth or material possessions through spiritual growth or intuition. | Impulsive or reckless behavior that leads to growth or change. |
